And until we personally hear both,

00:54:27.639 --> 00:54:30.639
it's best not to draw any conclusions.

00:54:30.639 --> 00:54:32.639
And even then,

00:54:32.639 --> 00:54:35.639
if it's something negative,

00:54:35.639 --> 00:54:37.639
we wouldn't want to spread it.

00:54:37.639 --> 00:54:40.639
Any more than we want something spread about ourselves.

00:54:40.639 --> 00:54:46.670
I'm going to consider that.

00:54:46.670 --> 00:54:47.670
Thanks.

00:54:47.670 --> 00:54:54.579
I'm going to apologise to Harry and Marie

00:54:54.579 --> 00:54:57.579
and have Emily talk directly to Haley.

00:54:57.579 --> 00:55:07.219
Good idea.

00:55:07.219 --> 00:55:09.219
Did you notice what Jake said

00:55:09.219 --> 00:55:12.219
after the elder graciously helped him reason

00:55:12.219 --> 00:55:15.219
on Proverbs 18, 17?

00:55:15.219 --> 00:55:16.219
He said,

00:55:16.219 --> 00:55:18.219
I had not considered that.

00:55:18.219 --> 00:55:20.219
Yes.

00:55:20.219 --> 00:55:23.219
Jake just did not stop and think

00:55:23.219 --> 00:55:27.219
before he said those negative things about Haley.

00:55:27.219 --> 00:55:30.219
So how can we put away harmful gossip

00:55:30.219 --> 00:55:32.219
before it begins?

00:55:32.219 --> 00:55:39.400
Let's read Proverbs 15, 28.

00:55:39.400 --> 00:55:41.400
The heart of the righteous one

00:55:41.400 --> 00:55:43.400
meditates before answering.

00:55:43.400 --> 00:55:45.400
But the mouth of the wicked

00:55:45.400 --> 00:55:49.400
blurs out bad things.

00:55:49.400 --> 00:55:52.400
So before we say bad things about others,

00:55:52.400 --> 00:55:55.400
we need to meditate.

00:55:55.400 --> 00:55:58.400
This does not mean a long drawn out process.

00:55:58.400 --> 00:56:01.400
It just requires a little thought.

00:56:01.400 --> 00:56:04.400
What thoughts could have stopped Jake

00:56:04.400 --> 00:56:07.400
from repeating his wife's negative view

00:56:07.400 --> 00:56:10.400
of Haley's post?

00:56:10.400 --> 00:56:12.400
He could have asked himself,

00:56:12.400 --> 00:56:15.400
is what I am about to say true?

00:56:15.400 --> 00:56:18.400
Is it kind, loving?

00:56:18.400 --> 00:56:20.400
How will Harry and Marie

00:56:20.400 --> 00:56:22.400
view Haley

00:56:22.400 --> 00:56:26.400
if they hear those negative things about her?

00:56:26.400 --> 00:56:28.400
Another principle that will help us

00:56:28.400 --> 00:56:30.400
to put away harmful gossip

00:56:30.400 --> 00:56:33.400
is the so-called Golden Rule

00:56:33.400 --> 00:56:36.400
as recorded at Luke 631.

00:56:36.400 --> 00:56:37.400
Jesus said,

00:56:37.400 --> 00:56:40.400
just as you want men to do to you

00:56:40.400 --> 00:56:43.400
do the same to them.

00:56:43.400 --> 00:56:46.400
This means showing empathy,

00:56:46.400 --> 00:56:49.400
putting ourselves in the place of the other person,

00:56:49.400 --> 00:56:50.400
asking ourselves,

00:56:50.400 --> 00:56:52.400
how would I feel

00:56:52.400 --> 00:56:56.710
if someone said this about me?

00:56:56.710 --> 00:56:58.710
One situation that may tempt us

00:56:58.710 --> 00:57:01.710
to engage in harmful gossip

00:57:01.710 --> 00:57:05.710
is when we believe we have been wronged by someone.

00:57:05.710 --> 00:57:07.710
Instead of applying the counsel

00:57:07.710 --> 00:57:10.710
at Matthew 5.23 and 24

00:57:10.710 --> 00:57:12.710
and chapter 18 verse 15

00:57:12.710 --> 00:57:15.710
to talk to the person privately,

00:57:15.710 --> 00:57:17.710
let's start talking about it to others

00:57:17.710 --> 00:57:19.710
who are not involved.

00:57:19.710 --> 00:57:23.710
Imagine if after finally talking with the person

00:57:23.710 --> 00:57:27.710
you find out he actually did not wrong you at all.

00:57:27.710 --> 00:57:31.710
You have made the situation much worse.

00:57:31.710 --> 00:57:33.710
But whether we are right or wrong,

00:57:33.710 --> 00:57:36.710
engaging in hurtful speech

00:57:36.710 --> 00:57:41.440
will never improve a situation.

00:57:41.440 --> 00:57:44.440
Gossip requires a speaker

00:57:44.440 --> 00:57:46.440
and a listener.

00:57:46.440 --> 00:57:50.440
Is it wrong to listen to harmful gossip?

00:57:50.440 --> 00:57:51.440
Yes.

00:57:51.440 --> 00:57:55.440
Note what Proverbs 174 says.

00:57:55.440 --> 00:57:58.440
A wicked man pays attention

00:57:58.440 --> 00:58:00.440
to hurtful speech

00:58:00.440 --> 00:58:02.440
and a deceptive man

00:58:02.440 --> 00:58:05.440
listens to a malicious tongue.

00:58:05.440 --> 00:58:07.440
Think about that.

00:58:07.440 --> 00:58:09.440
In God's eyes,

00:58:09.440 --> 00:58:12.440
if we listen to hurtful, malicious speech,

00:58:12.440 --> 00:58:15.440
we too bear a heavy responsibility

00:58:15.440 --> 00:58:17.440
by listening to the gossiper,

00:58:17.440 --> 00:58:20.440
we are encouraging him to go on.

00:58:20.440 --> 00:58:23.440
So what should you do?

00:58:23.440 --> 00:58:26.440
Without taking on an air of self-righteousness,

00:58:26.440 --> 00:58:28.440
you could simply say,

00:58:28.440 --> 00:58:31.440
let's change the subject.

00:58:31.440 --> 00:58:35.440
Or I don't really feel comfortable talking about this.

00:58:35.440 --> 00:58:40.440
After all, she is not here to defend herself.

00:58:40.440 --> 00:58:44.440
And if we find that her brother or sister likes to gossip,

00:58:44.440 --> 00:58:48.440
we may find it easier to avoid harmful gossip

00:58:48.440 --> 00:58:53.440
by stopping close association with that person.

00:58:53.440 --> 00:58:56.440
Proverbs 20 verse 19,

00:58:56.440 --> 00:58:59.440
frankly, councils do not associate

00:58:59.440 --> 00:59:03.440
with one who loves to gossip.

00:59:03.440 --> 00:59:05.440
So dear friends,

00:59:05.440 --> 00:59:08.440
let's put away harmful gossip

00:59:08.440 --> 00:59:13.440
doing so we will maintain our precious peace and unity.

00:59:14.440 --> 00:59:18.440
Brother Kenneth Cook, a member of the governing body,

00:59:18.440 --> 00:59:22.440
will now present the final talk of this symposium,

00:59:22.440 --> 00:59:24.440
put away peace records,

00:59:24.440 --> 00:59:34.960
uncontrolled anger.

00:59:34.960 --> 00:59:37.960
Satan is the main peace record.

00:59:37.960 --> 00:59:41.960
The scriptures tell us that he is driven by great anger.

00:59:41.960 --> 00:59:45.960
His anger is malicious and uncontrolled.

00:59:45.960 --> 00:59:48.960
Would any sound-minded God-fearing person

00:59:48.960 --> 00:59:52.960
allow himself to reflect Satan's vicious anger?

00:59:52.960 --> 00:59:54.960
Of course not.

00:59:54.960 --> 00:59:57.960
That is why all true servants of God are determined

00:59:57.960 --> 01:00:00.960
to put away uncontrolled anger.

01:00:00.960 --> 01:00:03.960
But apart from uncontrolled anger,

01:00:03.960 --> 01:00:05.960
is all anger bad?

01:00:05.960 --> 01:00:08.960
The Bible does not condemn all anger.

01:00:08.960 --> 01:00:12.960
It teaches us that anger is wrong when it is uncontrolled

01:00:12.960 --> 01:00:14.960
or unjustified.

01:00:14.960 --> 01:00:18.960
In Ephesians 426, God's Word tells us to be wrathful,

01:00:18.960 --> 01:00:21.960
but it adds do not sin.

01:00:21.960 --> 01:00:24.960
At times, anger may simply be a strong feeling

01:00:24.960 --> 01:00:28.960
that comes into us because of being upset or annoyed

01:00:28.960 --> 01:00:31.960
by something that we see as being wrong.

01:00:31.960 --> 01:00:34.960
That in itself is not bad.

01:00:34.960 --> 01:00:39.960
But what makes anger bad is when it fills a person's heart.

01:00:39.960 --> 01:00:42.960
And here she just loses control of it.

01:00:42.960 --> 01:00:43.960
That happens.

01:00:43.960 --> 01:00:48.960
It may cause a person to act without a sound mind.

01:00:48.960 --> 01:00:50.960
Those who continue to lash out in anger

01:00:50.960 --> 01:00:53.960
will not gain salvation.

01:00:53.960 --> 01:00:57.960
Galatians 520 lists fits of anger among the works of the flesh

01:00:57.960 --> 01:01:02.960
that will prevent a person from inheriting God's kingdom.

01:01:02.960 --> 01:01:06.960
There will be no place for such ones in God's new world.

01:01:06.960 --> 01:01:09.960
A brief review of how uncontrolled anger wrecks peace

01:01:09.960 --> 01:01:14.960
for ourselves and others will highlight why this is so.

01:01:14.960 --> 01:01:18.960
Uncontrolled anger harms both the angry person

01:01:18.960 --> 01:01:20.960
as well as those around him.

01:01:20.960 --> 01:01:23.960
We read at Proverbs 29-22

01:01:23.960 --> 01:01:26.960
that an angry person stirs up strife

01:01:26.960 --> 01:01:30.960
adding that he commits many transgressions.

01:01:30.960 --> 01:01:34.960
One of these many sins is abusive speech.

01:01:34.960 --> 01:01:38.960
We must work to show restraint when speaking with workmates,

01:01:38.960 --> 01:01:40.960
with strangers in the ministry,

01:01:40.960 --> 01:01:44.960
with our brothers and sisters in the congregation,

01:01:44.960 --> 01:01:46.960
and with our family members.

01:01:46.960 --> 01:01:49.960
Bad feelings must be controlled.

01:01:49.960 --> 01:01:55.960
Abusive speech, ridicule, contempt, and hateful anger are wrong.

01:01:55.960 --> 01:01:59.960
Giving vent to such feelings can destroy precious friendships

01:01:59.960 --> 01:02:03.960
with other people and with Jehovah.

01:02:03.960 --> 01:02:05.960
Don't be like a volcano.

01:02:05.960 --> 01:02:07.960
That will not quiet down.

01:02:07.960 --> 01:02:10.960
Just like an erupting volcano

01:02:10.960 --> 01:02:12.960
will harm those living around it.

01:02:12.960 --> 01:02:15.960
So too a person who expresses intense anger

01:02:15.960 --> 01:02:18.960
will harm those living around him.

01:02:18.960 --> 01:02:23.960
He also damages himself in what way?

01:02:23.960 --> 01:02:28.960
Acting on anger often leads to even more aggression.

01:02:28.960 --> 01:02:32.960
So then uncontrolled anger can also affect our own peace.

01:02:32.960 --> 01:02:36.960
It can cause us to do something that we will later regret.

01:02:36.960 --> 01:02:39.960
It can have a negative effect on our health.

01:02:39.960 --> 01:02:43.960
Medical studies show that uncontrolled anger can cause

01:02:43.960 --> 01:02:46.960
high blood pressure and respiratory problems.

01:02:46.960 --> 01:02:49.960
It can also affect the liver and pancreas.

01:02:49.960 --> 01:02:53.960
And such anger can cause digestive problems.

01:02:53.960 --> 01:02:55.960
When a person becomes angry,

01:02:55.960 --> 01:02:58.960
he or she will not always think clearly.

01:02:58.960 --> 01:03:03.960
After a fit of rage, a person may become depressed.

01:03:03.960 --> 01:03:07.960
No wonder we read at Proverbs 14 and verse 30

01:03:07.960 --> 01:03:12.960
that a calm heart gives life to the body.

01:03:12.960 --> 01:03:15.960
The disastrous consequences of uncontrolled anger

01:03:15.960 --> 01:03:20.960
are illustrated in God's word by the actions of Simeon

01:03:20.960 --> 01:03:24.960
and Levi, sons of the patriarch Jacob.

01:03:24.960 --> 01:03:27.960
When they learned that their sister Dino was violated

01:03:27.960 --> 01:03:29.960
by a man named Shikam,

01:03:29.960 --> 01:03:32.960
we read a Genesis 34 and verse 7

01:03:32.960 --> 01:03:36.960
that they were offended and very angry.

01:03:36.960 --> 01:03:38.960
Now they had a valid reason to be angry,

01:03:38.960 --> 01:03:41.960
but they took their anger too far.

01:03:41.960 --> 01:03:43.960
It was uncontrolled.

01:03:43.960 --> 01:03:46.960
Simeon and Levi took vengeance on Shikam.

01:03:46.960 --> 01:03:48.960
Using deception,

01:03:48.960 --> 01:03:53.960
they attacked and killed every male in Shikam city.

01:03:53.960 --> 01:03:56.960
Then, along with the other sons of Jacob,

01:03:56.960 --> 01:03:58.960
they plundered it and took the women

01:03:58.960 --> 01:04:01.960
and little children captive.

01:04:01.960 --> 01:04:06.960
Dino's tragic experience must have grieved Jacob greatly,

01:04:06.960 --> 01:04:11.960
yet he condemned his son's uncontrolled anger.

01:04:11.960 --> 01:04:14.960
Simeon and Levi tried to justify their actions,

01:04:14.960 --> 01:04:16.960
but that was not the end of the matter

01:04:16.960 --> 01:04:20.960
because Jehovah was also displeased.

01:04:20.960 --> 01:04:23.960
For this reason, Jacob later foretold

01:04:23.960 --> 01:04:26.960
that the descendants of Simeon and Levi

01:04:26.960 --> 01:04:30.960
were to be scattered among the tribes of Israel.

01:04:30.960 --> 01:04:34.960
Their uncontrolled anger brought disfavor from God

01:04:34.960 --> 01:04:37.960
and from their father, Jacob.

01:04:37.960 --> 01:04:41.960
We're wise to pay attention to such scriptural accounts

01:04:41.960 --> 01:04:44.960
and put away uncontrolled anger

01:04:44.960 --> 01:04:47.960
and all of the harm that it brings.

