01:07:26.590 --> 01:07:30.590
Now that we've defined uncontrolled anger

01:07:30.590 --> 01:07:33.590
and considered what it can lead to,

01:07:33.590 --> 01:07:35.590
the next question is,

01:07:35.590 --> 01:07:39.590
how can we put away uncontrolled anger?

01:07:39.590 --> 01:07:44.590
First, we need to recognize the danger of uncontrolled anger.

01:07:44.590 --> 01:07:46.590
Proverbs 25-28 states,

01:07:46.590 --> 01:07:50.590
that as a city broken through without a wall,

01:07:50.590 --> 01:07:54.590
is the man who cannot control his temper.

01:07:54.590 --> 01:07:58.590
Strong city walls were vital in ancient times.

01:07:58.590 --> 01:08:01.590
Without them, a city would quickly fall to invaders,

01:08:01.590 --> 01:08:02.590
likewise.

01:08:02.590 --> 01:08:05.590
So will those who cannot control their temper.

01:08:06.590 --> 01:08:10.590
By losing control, they make themselves vulnerable

01:08:10.590 --> 01:08:13.590
to the invasion of wrong thoughts,

01:08:13.590 --> 01:08:16.590
thoughts that can cause them to hurt themselves,

01:08:16.590 --> 01:08:17.590
and others.

01:08:17.590 --> 01:08:21.590
Uncontrolled anger can do just that.

01:08:21.590 --> 01:08:24.590
Next, after recognizing the danger,

01:08:24.590 --> 01:08:28.590
we must pause and then deal with the anger

01:08:28.590 --> 01:08:32.590
