01:32:18.979 --> 01:32:25.979
These actions contributed to the peaceful conditions that elevated pure worship.

01:32:25.979 --> 01:32:28.979
Josiah did so much to restore pure worship.

01:32:28.979 --> 01:32:33.979
That is why we love him, yet the people's heart condition remained polluted,

01:32:33.979 --> 01:32:37.979
so the nation required severe discipline.

01:32:37.979 --> 01:32:42.979
Jeremiah prophesied a conquest of the Babylonians against Judah.

01:32:42.979 --> 01:32:46.979
All this land will be reduced to ruins,

01:32:46.979 --> 01:32:52.979
and this land and its inhabitants will have to serve the king of Babylon for 70 years.

01:32:52.979 --> 01:32:56.979
Daniel himself may have heard Jeremiah speak those words,

01:32:56.979 --> 01:33:03.300
and he certainly saw it come true as he and his family were exiled to Babylon.

01:33:03.300 --> 01:33:05.300
Talk about peace being interrupted.

01:33:05.300 --> 01:33:14.050
Daniel was a young Judean prince taken from his homeland, separated from his family,

01:33:14.050 --> 01:33:19.050
but being chosen to receive special training in the court of King Nebuchadnezzar,

01:33:19.050 --> 01:33:22.050
represented another set of challenges.

01:33:22.050 --> 01:33:28.050
The entire way of Babylonian life was contrary to a Daniel knew growing up in Judah,

01:33:28.050 --> 01:33:35.050
but Daniel was determined not to pollute himself, with foods Jehovah would not approve of.

01:33:35.050 --> 01:33:39.619
And Jehovah blessed Daniel's determination to be faithful,

01:33:39.619 --> 01:33:44.619
as he was selected to serve as one of King Nebuchadnezzar's wise men.

01:33:44.619 --> 01:33:57.619
Nebuchadnezzar was a warrior king intent on building a great empire.

01:33:58.619 --> 01:34:05.619
After he officially took the throne in 624 BCE, his domain grew with each conquest.

01:34:05.619 --> 01:34:11.600
Babylon became an epicenter of trade and commerce.

01:34:11.600 --> 01:34:18.600
Nebuchadnezzar undertook huge building projects throughout the city, which made the city seem impregnable.

01:34:18.600 --> 01:34:23.600
Imagine the sense of security, the inhabitants of Babylon must have felt,

01:34:23.600 --> 01:34:28.140
what safely behind the city's walls.

01:34:28.140 --> 01:34:35.140
Nebuchadnezzar attributed the prosperity and security all around him to the power of his false gods.

01:34:35.140 --> 01:34:39.140
The chief of these false gods was Marduk, the god of war.

01:34:39.140 --> 01:34:45.699
Yet these false gods and their priests would prove worthless.

01:34:45.699 --> 01:34:50.699
One night, King Nebuchadnezzar had a strange dream.

01:34:50.699 --> 01:35:05.600
Hey, may you live on forever.

01:35:05.600 --> 01:35:06.600
Relate the dream to your service.

01:35:06.600 --> 01:35:08.600
We will tell the interpretation.

01:35:08.600 --> 01:35:09.600
No.

01:35:09.600 --> 01:35:14.600
If you don't make the dream known to me, along with the interpretation, you'll be dismembered.

01:35:14.600 --> 01:35:18.600
And your houses will be turned to public latrines.

01:35:18.600 --> 01:35:22.600
There is not a man on earth who can do with the King demands.

01:35:22.600 --> 01:35:24.600
What the King is asking is difficult.

01:35:24.600 --> 01:35:25.600
No one exists.

01:35:25.600 --> 01:35:35.810
Can tell this to the King except the gods.

01:35:35.810 --> 01:35:36.810
Seize them.

01:35:36.810 --> 01:35:39.630
Kill them!

01:35:39.630 --> 01:35:43.130
Kira.

01:35:43.130 --> 01:35:44.130
You're in danger.

01:35:44.130 --> 01:35:45.130
Why what happened?

01:35:45.130 --> 01:35:46.130
He hears.

01:35:46.130 --> 01:35:48.130
But the wise man angered the King.

01:35:48.130 --> 01:35:50.130
Everyone's to be executed by dawn.

01:35:50.130 --> 01:35:54.130
Bring Hanna and I, Michelle, and Ezraia here.

01:35:54.130 --> 01:35:56.130
I'll try to learn more.

01:35:56.130 --> 01:36:01.130
This edict to kill all the wise men would also include Daniel and his companions.

01:36:01.130 --> 01:36:04.130
So let's look at this from Daniel's perspective.

01:36:04.130 --> 01:36:11.130
Here he is, young man in a foreign land, serving in the court of one of the most powerful and violent men alive.

01:36:11.130 --> 01:36:16.130
And that man is now demanding that someone in effect read his mind.

01:36:16.130 --> 01:36:22.300
Tell me my dream and tell me what it means.

01:36:22.300 --> 01:36:23.300
Okay.

01:36:24.300 --> 01:36:27.300
Interpretations belong to my God, Jehovah.

01:36:27.300 --> 01:36:30.300
He knows your dream and what it means.

01:36:30.300 --> 01:36:34.449
Well, where is your God?

01:36:34.449 --> 01:36:37.689
Where?

01:36:37.689 --> 01:36:39.689
I believe that he...

01:36:39.689 --> 01:36:42.689
I know that he will reveal it to me.

01:36:42.689 --> 01:36:44.689
Please, give me time.

01:36:44.689 --> 01:36:51.279
Daniel is not acting on previous experience.

01:36:51.279 --> 01:36:55.279
He hasn't received interpretations of dreams from Jehovah.

01:36:55.279 --> 01:37:02.279
Instead, he is acting on faith, faith that he had learned by studying the sacred books of his time.

01:37:02.279 --> 01:37:11.279
These books likely included the inspired writings of Moses and David Solomon, Isaiah, Jeremiah, and other prophets.

01:37:11.279 --> 01:37:14.279
Oh, we can only imagine Daniel.

01:37:14.279 --> 01:37:23.279
Pouring over these scrolls, opening up his heart to Jehovah begging Jehovah to give him wisdom and understanding, he loved it.

01:37:23.279 --> 01:37:33.279
And there's no doubt that as Daniel studied these accounts, his faith was strengthened and his bond with Jehovah drew even closer.

01:37:33.279 --> 01:37:43.279
Even though Daniel knew nothing of King Nebuchadnezzar's dream, he was fully convinced that Jehovah would reveal the dream and its interpretation.

01:37:43.279 --> 01:37:47.279
And proved to be Daniel's salvation.

01:37:47.279 --> 01:37:52.279
Do we know exactly which accounts Daniel was able to draw from at this time?

01:37:52.279 --> 01:37:58.279
It's impossible to say for a certainty, but we do know he had access to the books.

01:37:58.279 --> 01:38:01.279
He references the prophecies of Jeremiah.

01:38:01.279 --> 01:38:06.279
Daniel could see how Jehovah blessed faithful, obedient men in the past.

01:38:06.279 --> 01:38:11.279
So by asking Nebuchadnezzar for time, he wasn't looking to buy himself another day of life.

01:38:11.279 --> 01:38:16.279
He was allowing Jehovah to reward his faith by revealing the dream to him.

01:38:16.279 --> 01:38:22.939
Daniel strikes a balance here.

01:38:22.939 --> 01:38:31.939
Although he is confident that Jehovah will reveal the dream to him, he isn't casual in the way he handled the situation.

01:38:31.939 --> 01:38:35.939
He did what any God-fearing man would do here.

01:38:35.939 --> 01:38:39.939
He approached Jehovah in prayer.

01:38:39.939 --> 01:38:44.939
Oh Jehovah, surely you didn't bring us here just to die.

01:38:44.939 --> 01:38:47.939
What will people say?

01:38:47.939 --> 01:38:54.939
We told them that you are the God of the heavens, the only God who can reveal secrets.

01:38:54.939 --> 01:39:00.500
Please, vindicate yourself.

01:39:00.500 --> 01:39:43.189
The man from the axiles of Judah, who can make known the interpretation to the King.

01:39:43.189 --> 01:39:47.369
I know who he is.

01:39:47.369 --> 01:39:51.369
Can you really make known to me the dream that I saw and its interpretation?

01:39:51.369 --> 01:40:09.800
There is a God in the heavens who is a revealer of secrets.

01:40:09.800 --> 01:40:18.710
And he has made known to King Nebuchadnezzar what is to happen in the final part of the days.

01:40:18.710 --> 01:40:20.710
This is your dream.

01:40:20.710 --> 01:40:39.649
You saw an immense image.

01:40:39.649 --> 01:40:42.649
That image was standing in front of you.

01:40:42.649 --> 01:40:50.300
You yourself are the head of gold.

01:40:50.300 --> 01:40:55.300
After you, another kingdom will rise and fear you to you.

01:40:55.300 --> 01:40:58.300
Then another kingdom.

01:40:58.300 --> 01:41:03.300
A third one of copper that will rule over the whole earth.

01:41:03.300 --> 01:41:10.220
As for the fourth kingdom, it will be strong like iron.

01:41:10.220 --> 01:41:13.220
The kingdom will be divided.

01:41:13.220 --> 01:41:18.220
And as the toes of the feet were partly of iron and partly of clay,

01:41:18.220 --> 01:41:26.479
so the kingdom will be partly strong and partly fragile.

01:41:26.479 --> 01:41:31.479
This took a tremendous amount of faith and courage on the part of Daniel.

01:41:31.479 --> 01:41:34.479
Now we may find our peace threatened.

01:41:34.479 --> 01:41:37.479
Our very lives might be on the line.

01:41:37.479 --> 01:41:43.479
In that moment, we can turn to Jehovah God in prayer, opening up our hearts,

01:41:43.479 --> 01:41:47.479
confident that He will support us.

01:41:47.479 --> 01:41:52.479
Like both Daniel and Jonah, we've been given an assignment to proclaim a message.

01:41:52.479 --> 01:41:57.479
This requires courage to speak out boldly concerning Jehovah's judgments

01:41:57.479 --> 01:42:00.479
against those who oppose his sovereignty.

01:42:00.479 --> 01:42:07.479
Both of these prophets are excellent examples of Jehovah backing those who trust in Him.

01:42:07.479 --> 01:42:12.479
Jehovah will always be with us as long as we have faith in Him.

01:42:12.479 --> 01:42:17.479
When we face situations that seem impossible as in the case with Hezekiah,

01:42:17.479 --> 01:42:23.479
we have the ability to tap into the most powerful force there is.

01:42:23.479 --> 01:42:26.479
As this system comes to a close,

01:42:26.479 --> 01:42:32.479
we will find ourselves in situations that test our courage and threaten our peace.

01:42:32.479 --> 01:42:37.479
We will have to stand up for pure worship, just like Josiah,

01:42:37.479 --> 01:42:39.479
and this will be unpopular.

01:42:39.479 --> 01:42:44.479
But with Jehovah on our side, we can face those situations with confidence.

01:42:44.479 --> 01:42:48.479
He's all powerful, and He's going to help us through it.

01:42:48.479 --> 01:42:51.479
Now here's the interesting thing.

01:42:51.479 --> 01:42:59.479
Some of the prophecies that Daniel recorded applied not only to the future of the Babylonian Empire,

01:42:59.479 --> 01:43:05.479
but also outline world events to our day and beyond.

01:43:05.479 --> 01:43:12.479
And these events are being fulfilled right before our very eyes.

01:43:12.479 --> 01:43:23.130
What a motivating presentation.

01:43:23.130 --> 01:43:26.130
Even when our peace is threatened,

01:43:26.130 --> 01:43:31.130
we can focus on how our integrity relates to Jehovah's purpose,

01:43:31.130 --> 01:43:35.130
and we can endure with joy.

01:43:35.130 --> 01:43:39.130
We look forward to watching part two of this important consideration

01:43:39.130 --> 01:43:42.130
during the final session of our convention.

01:43:42.130 --> 01:43:47.130
Now let's sing together song number 130, entitled,

01:43:47.130 --> 01:43:51.130
Be Forgiven, that song number 130.
